## <a id="2-7-1"></a> v2.7.1

**Release Date: October 10, 2019**

### Features

New features and changes in this release:

* <%= vars.product_name %> supports a beta <%= vars.single_leader_plan %> service plan. This plan has the 
following features:
    + Replication across two routable <%= vars.app_runtime_full %> foundations secured over mTLS. The primary node in a foundation only trusts the secondary node in another foundation.
    + The ability to bind and push apps to a primary node a foundation and optionally, to a secondary node in another foundation. 
    <p class="note warning"><strong>Warning:</strong> <%= vars.single_leader_plan %> are for advanced use cases only. If you are interested in testing <%= vars.single_leader_plan %> service plans,
    contact <a href="https://pivotal.io/support"> Pivotal Support</a>. 
  </p>
* Updates Percona Server to v5.7.26-29.
* Highly available (HA) cluster plans are now in general availability (GA). 
* Updates pxc-release to 0.20.0.
* Updates envoy to v1.3.1.

### Security Fix

This release includes the following security update:

* Updates the bpm-release to v1.1.3. This update fixes Medium [CVE-2019-9893](https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2019-9893).

### Resolved Issues

This release has the following fixes:

* You can now share MySQL for Pivotal Platform service instances across orgs and spaces using `cf share-service`.

### Known Issue

There are no known issues for this release.

## <a id="2-7-0"></a> v2.7.0

**Release Date: August 7, 2019**

### Features

New features and changes in this release:

* When you upgrade to <%= vars.product_name %> v2.7, <%= vars.product_name %> automatically rotates internal certificates
  and certificate authority (CA) certificates.
  The new certificates do not expire for 5 years. For more information,
  see [Managing Certificates](./rotating-ca.html).

* Automatic backups are now compatible with the AWS CLI v1.16.189,
  which defaults to Amazon S3 Signature Version 4 for S3 buckets when no other configuration is provided.


